    "body": "### Problem\n\nAs title says, I faced the issue with lsp inlay hint, and tested with a minimal init.lua with decoration provider, the same as how inlay hint set extmarks.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nvim.o.concealcursor = \"n\"\nlocal draw = false\nlocal ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"z\")\nvim.api.nvim_set_decoration_provider(ns, {\n    on_win = function()\n        if draw == true then\n            draw = false\n            vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 0, 0, {\n                virt_text_pos = \"inline\",\n                virt_text = { { \"VERTTEXT\", \"Comment\" } },\n            })\n        end\n    end,\n})\nvim.keymap.set(\"n\", \"f\", function()\n    draw = true\n    vim.cmd(\"redraw!\")\nend)\n```\n\ntype some text and press f, notice cursor don't get redrawn:\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0775c1be-dc4f-4838-bbad-94afb950e82c\n\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n cursor should shift right\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11 release\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacos 14.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nxterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from source",
